mediaNotes: vocalizing perched low just above thick swampy understory, around 10ft away from edge of road
Single song from a very close bird.
Single song repeated, about 5/min

Fast songs and calls primarily from one individual, then chase calls, flight songs, and typical songs from several other individuals in the area along with more from the focal individual. Mostly natural, last few segments after playback.

A male singing near the board walk. He is giving very quiet sneezing-like sounds between songs. His whole body shakes with each sneeze and his tail deflects downward. 30" Roche parabola, Sennhiser MKH 8020 mic, Sound Devices 702 with HPF at 80Hz, -12dB/octave.
At one,seven, and seventeen seconds. The reedy trill type call. Thought at first it was a Marsh Wren that was off on it's song.
